There's someone fixing my kitchen floor right now, and I'm pretending to have a job and work from home while I'm sitting on Too Hot to Handle.
If I could only bloody well open the file. (Damn One Drive.)
*Voice of a hacker* I'm in.
And that's exactly when he starts drilling extremely loudly. Hurrah.
It feels somewhat passive-aggressive to turn up my air purifier to the maximum, but I can smell the wood dust, so it would be completely fine even if he wasn't a mask opponent. And do I really have to protect myself?
I would really like to go back to bed, but I can't until he leaves.
At least I finally finished revising Chapter 4!
Chapter 5 is long, but so damn frightening. Oh yes, that's the good stuff!
I'm doing Find and Replace for … ➡️ Ellipses Symbol and there are 54 in this chapter 😅
But no, I'm sticking to it. Natural language is usually chopped up, especially when one gets emotional.
The handyman is now using the vacuum cleaner. Hopefully, that means he's finishing up soon.
He has gone out to cut something (at least that's what it sounds like). I quietly checked how far he is. There's still a lot to do :(
Still 7 pages in Chapter 5. It's still my favorite chapter and it's quite good – mainly changes to the font and very small corrections on direct speech and I need to rephrase everything to make it more compact. But I could really use a break and a cup of tea right now, but that guy is still in my kitchen.
He's started vacuuming again now. Hopefully, that's a good sign.
The kitchen guy is gone!
He told me that he made an estimate for the entire floor, but the landlords were being stingy and only paid for the part next to the door, which is no longer in order. Feels just as good.
The house is being ventilated and in the kitchen my air purifier is running, while I'm having a tea in the garden!
